00:04:14.224 --> 00:04:20.194
AI is the ability of a computer or
machine to seem intelligent, to answer

00:04:20.194 --> 00:04:23.024
questions or do things like a human.

00:04:24.174 --> 00:04:28.394
Think about how you, as a human
being, respond to a question.

00:04:28.894 --> 00:04:33.034
You listen, understand what you
are being asked, and then you

00:04:33.214 --> 00:04:37.453
consult the information available
to you, based on your experience

00:04:37.633 --> 00:04:39.193
and knowledge, to give an answer.

00:04:40.193 --> 00:04:45.083
Perhaps this is an easy question, like:
“What’s your name, or is it raining?”

00:04:45.973 --> 00:04:51.323
Or maybe it’s a harder one, like: “What
were the reasons for the Great Depression

00:04:51.543 --> 00:04:56.573
or what circumstances could have led
to the Titanic not sinking so quickly?”

00:04:57.283 --> 00:05:03.613
Or maybe it’s an even harder one, like,
“How can we reduce global warming or how

00:05:03.613 --> 00:05:06.363
can our country improve health outcomes?”

00:05:07.423 --> 00:05:12.683
In all of these cases, to try to
answer these questions, you consult the

00:05:12.683 --> 00:05:17.953
information available to you, analyse
that information, and provide an answer.

00:05:19.353 --> 00:05:23.113
Artificial Intelligence
works on a similar principle.

00:05:23.683 --> 00:05:29.523
It is a set of algorithms that analyse
a large amount of data, learn from

00:05:29.523 --> 00:05:34.903
this data, and then do things, do
whatever you ask, based on that data.

00:05:35.863 --> 00:05:39.123
